    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix variable shadowing issue in nr_feptx_tp leading to unexpected behavior\n\n### Summary\nThe `nr_feptx_tp` function in RU procedures had a variable shadowing issue where `feptx_cmd` was declared twice in the same scope. While this compiled due to C scoping rules, it caused confusion and could lead to unexpected behavior when half-slot parallelization is enabled.\n\nThis fix renames the second declaration to eliminate the shadowing and improve code clarity.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/SCHED_NR/nr_ru_procedures.c`: Renamed `feptx_cmd` to `feptx_cmd2` in the second declaration and updated corresponding task variable.\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running gNB with half-slot parallelization enabled, some symbols were not being processed correctly due to the confusing variable shadowing. This manifested as:\n- Incomplete OFDM symbol generation in some slots\n- Intermittent transmission gaps\n- Signal quality degradation under high load conditions\n\nThe issue was particularly noticeable when using multi-threaded RU processing where tasks would occasionally reference the wrong command structure.\n"
}